Package: rgeoadaptels
Type: Package
Title: Scale-Adaptive Superpixels for Geospatial Raster Data
Version: 0.3.1
Authors@R: person("Igor", "Pawelec", email = "igor.pawelec@urk.edu.pl",
                  role = c("aut", "cre"),
                  comment = c(ORCID = "0009-0005-9798-3596"))
Description: Segments a raster into scale-adaptive superpixels, or adaptels.
    Regions grow from a seed until their internal distance passes a
    threshold and the pixels beyond it become seeds in turn, so the number
    of segments follows the scene instead of being fixed in advance.
    Minkowski, cosine and angular distances are provided, each on its own
    scale. Also implements SICLE, which starts from far more seeds than
    wanted, grows an optimum-path forest and discards the least relevant
    seeds until the requested count remains, following Belem and others
    (2023) <doi:10.1007/s10851-023-01156-9>. Written in R and plain C with no compiled dependencies and no
    required packages. Methods follow Achanta and others (2018),
    'Scale-Adaptive Superpixels', Color and Imaging Conference.
License: GPL-3
